texinfo.txi(,3) @c Ordinarily Texinfo files have the extension .texi.  But texinfo.texi
texinfo.txi(,4) @c clashes with texinfo.tex on 8.3 filesystems, so we use texinfo.txi.
texinfo.txi(,5) 
